===============================================================================
INTRODUCE
===============================================================================

SYNTAX:
  introduce <name>

DESCRIPTION:
  Introduce yourself to others in the room, telling them your name.
  
  Before introduction, others see you as "a <race> <description>".
  After introduction, they'll recognize you by name during the session.
  
  For permanent recognition across sessions, others must use the
  'remember' command.

EXAMPLES:
  > introduce Marcus
  You introduce yourself as Marcus.
  
  > introduce Shadowblade
  You introduce yourself as Shadowblade.

WHAT OTHERS SEE:
  "A tall human warrior introduces themselves as Marcus."
  "The great horned dragon introduces themselves as Shadowblade."

NOTES:
  - You can introduce yourself with any name
  - Introductions last for the current session
  - Others must use 'remember' to make it permanent
  - Your surname is separate (see 'help surname')
  - Part of the identity system (see 'help identity')

RELATED COMMANDS:
  remember  - Permanently remember someone's identity
  forget    - Forget someone's identity
  surname   - Set or change your surname
  who       - See who's online (shows introduced names)

===============================================================================
See also: help identity, help remember, help forget
===============================================================================
